Function to extract basic information from the image.¶

In [7]:
def basic_image_info(df,path):
    image_name=[]
    img_mode=[]
    img_height=[]
    img_width=[]
    for file in df['img']:
        image_name.append(file)
        img=Image.open(f"{(os.path.join(path, file))}")
        img_mode.append(img.mode)
        img_width.append(img.width)
        img_height.append(img.height)


    return pd.DataFrame({'image_name':image_name,'img_mode':img_mode,'img_width':img_width,'img_height':img_height})

Function to read the image¶

In [14]:
def img_read(path,im ,new_size=False):
    img = Image.open(f"{(os.path.join(path, im))}")
    #img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    if new_size:
        img=img.resize((224,224))
        return img
    else:
        return img

Let's calculate the hash value of the image by using different hashing algorithms. Then,find similar images based on different hash algorithms.¶

In [19]:
def get_image_hash(path):
    image_name=[]
    img_avg_hash=[]
    img_phash=[]
    img_dhash=[]
    img_whash=[]
    img_color_hash=[]
    for img in train['img']:
        image_name.append(img)
        img=Image.open(f"{(os.path.join(path, img))}")
        img_avg_hash.append(imagehash.average_hash(img))
        img_phash.append(imagehash.phash(img))
        img_dhash.append(imagehash.dhash(img))
        img_whash.append(imagehash.whash(img))
        img_color_hash.append(imagehash.colorhash(img))
               

    return pd.DataFrame({'image_name':image_name,'img_avg_hash':img_avg_hash,'img_phash':img_phash,'img_dhash':img_dhash,
                             'img_whash':img_whash,'img_color_hash':img_color_hash})
In [20]:
train_hash_info=get_image_hash("/kaggle/input/data-centric-ai-competition-2023-image-data/train/")

Function to find similar images.¶

In [21]:
def image_simliarity(path,df,hash_type,hash_name ,return_df=False):
    img_and_hash=[(i,j) for i,j in zip(list(df['image_name']),list(df[hash_type].astype('str')))]
    ref_image=[]
    similar_img=[]
    for img1, img2 in itertools.combinations(img_and_hash,2):
        f1, hash1 = img1
        f2, hash2 = img2
        hashdif = distance.hamming(hash1, hash2)
        if hashdif < 5: 
        #print(f"images are similar due to dhash", "image1", f1, "image2", f2)
            ref_image.append(f1)
            similar_img.append(f2)
    if return_df:
        return pd.DataFrame({'reference_image':ref_image,'similar_image':similar_img})
    else:
        print(f"Total Similar Images Based on {hash_name} Algorithm {len(ref_image)}")
        for image1,image2 in zip(ref_image[:10],similar_img[:10]):
            fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2 ,figsize=(10, 8))
            img1=img_read(path,image1)
            axs[0].imshow(img_read(path,df[df['image_name']==image1]['image_name'].head(1).values[0],new_size=512))
            axs[0].axis('off')
            axs[0].set_title(f"Reference Image {image1}")
            img2=img_read(path,image2)
            axs[1].imshow(img_read(path,df[df['image_name']==image2]['image_name'].head(1).values[0],new_size=512))
            axs[1].axis('off')
            axs[1].set_title(f"Matched Image {image2}")
        plt.show()
